"n.评判的标准，尺度 【英】 n. 评判的标准,尺度(sta ndard by which sth. is judged) 【记】 crit(判断,分辨)+er+ ion→标准 n. (作出判断或决定的)评判标准, 尺度 【记】crit判断, 区分, 评判－判断的标准 【参】critique(n 批评) 【记】critical + on 批评的标准 criterion (n.)  1660s, from Latinized form of Greek kriterion ""means for judging, standard,"" from krites ""judge,"" from PIE root *krei- (see crisis). Used in English as a Greek word from 1610s."
